    "body": "IN THE UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT\n\nFOR THE DISTRICT AND DIVISION IN WHICH THE UNLAWFUL PRACTICES OCCURRED\n\n\n\nJane Doe, Plaintiff,\n\nv.\n\nAcme Corporation, Defendant.\n\n\n\nCivil Action No. ________________\n\nCOMPLAINT FOR RETALIATION\n\nJURY TRIAL DEMANDED\n\n\n\nPlaintiff Jane Doe, by and through this Complaint, alleges upon personal knowledge as to their own acts and upon information and belief as to all other matters, as follows:\n\n\n\nNATURE OF THE ACTION\n\n1. Jane Doe brings this retaliation complaint against Acme Corporation. This civil action arises from Acme Corporation's retaliatory response after Jane Doe Reported discrimination to HR.\n\n2. Plaintiff seeks damages, equitable relief, and any further relief necessary to remedy the retaliatory conduct, restore lost compensation, and prevent additional harm flowing from Termination two days later.\n\n\n\nJURISDICTION AND VENUE\n\n3. Jurisdiction is alleged in this Court because the controversy arises under retaliation law and related remedial doctrines applicable to the challenged conduct.\n\n4. Venue is alleged to be proper because a substantial part of the events or omissions giving rise to these claims occurred in this forum and the resulting harm was felt here.\n\n\n\nPARTIES\n\n5. Plaintiff Jane Doe is the person harmed by the retaliation described below.\n\n6. Defendant Acme Corporation is the party from whom relief is sought and is responsible for the retaliatory actions alleged in this pleading.\n\n\n\nFACTUAL ALLEGATIONS\n\n7. Jane Doe alleges that they Reported discrimination to HR.\n\n8. Plaintiff provided or attempted to provide protected information, opposition, reporting, or participation activity that should not have triggered reprisal.\n\n9. After that protected activity, Jane Doe experienced Termination two days later.\n\n10. The chronology currently available in the record shows that Report on March 8, termination on March 10.\n\n11. As a direct and proximate result of Defendant's conduct, Jane Doe suffered Lost wages and emotional distress.\n\n\n\nEVIDENTIARY SUPPORT AND NOTICE\n\n12. The current complaint record includes 21 saved evidence items, including testimony such as HR complaint email (protected_activity); HR complaint email (protected_activity); HR complaint email (protected_activity).\n\n13. The current documentary record includes the following summarized exhibits or records: No documentary exhibits have been summarized yet.\n\n14. The present support review reflects 5 supported claim elements and 0 open support gaps, which Plaintiff identifies so the pleading can be refined rather than to concede any deficiency in the claim.\n\n15. Plaintiff incorporates the current testimony summaries, documentary exhibits, chronology notes, and support review findings as the preliminary exhibit and notice record for this pleading.\n\n16. Plaintiff testimony or witness account titled 'HR complaint email' supports protected_activity.\n\n17. Plaintiff testimony or witness account titled 'HR complaint email' supports protected_activity.\n\n\n\nCLAIM FOR RELIEF\n\nCOUNT I - RETALIATION\n\n18. Jane Doe repeats and realleges the preceding paragraphs as if fully set forth herein.\n\n19. Jane Doe engaged in protected activity by Reported discrimination to HR, and Defendant knew or should have known of that protected conduct.\n\n20. Defendant thereafter subjected Plaintiff to materially adverse action, including Termination two days later, under circumstances supporting retaliatory motive and causation.\n\n21. The pleaded chronology, evidentiary record, and resulting harm support a plausible retaliation claim because protected activity was followed by materially adverse conduct and damages.\n\n22. Plaintiff has suffered damages and other losses including Lost wages and emotional distress.\n\n23. Defendant's acts were intentional, knowing, reckless, retaliatory, discriminatory, deceptive, or otherwise unlawful under the governing claim theory.\n\n\n\nPRAYER FOR RELIEF\n\nWherefore, Plaintiff requests judgment against Defendant and the following relief:\n\n1. Compensatory damages.\n2. Back pay.\n3. Injunctive relief.\n\n\n\nJURY DEMAND\n\nPlaintiff demands a trial by jury on all issues so triable.\n\n\n\nSIGNATURE BLOCK\n\nDated: ____________________\n\n\n\nRespectfully submitted,\n\n\n\nJane Doe\n\nPlaintiff, Pro Se\n\nAddress: ____________________\n\nTelephone: ____________________\n\nEmail: ____________________\n\n\n\nWORKING CASE SYNOPSIS\n\nWorking case synopsis: Jane Doe is pursuing a retaliation complaint against Acme Corporation. The current theory is that Jane Doe Reported discrimination to HR, then experienced Termination two days later. The reported harm is Lost wages and emotional distress. Timeline posture: Report on March 8, termination on March 10. Current support posture: 5 supported elements, 0 open gaps, 21 saved evidence items.",
